{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Liu et al. (2023c) conducted an empirical evaluation on 78 jailbreak prompts from Jailbreakchat and categorized their attacking mechanisms into three categories: privilege escalation, pretending, and attention shifting.",
    "DAN (Shen et al., 2023) conducted a wider analysis on 6,387 prompts collected from four platforms and identified two highly effective jailbreak prompts.",
    "The two empirical evaluations contributed to the advancement of creative hand-crafted prompt design.",
    "Yong et al. (2023) exposed the inherent cross-lingual vulnerability of the safeguards and attacked GPT-4 through translating harmful English questions into low-resource languages.",
    "DeepInception (Li et al., 2023b) leveraged the personification ability of LLMs to construct a nested hypothetical scene for jailbreak."
  ],
